enTitle: China and North Korean Border in Heavy Fog
enDesc: The China and North Korea border bridge disappears in the heavy fog.
The old bridge was destroyed by the war.

enTitle: A Little Girl in Korean Costume
enDesc: There are a few venders lending North Korean costumes. A little girl has her photo taken in costumes.
A fishing boat on Yalu River in heavy fog.
A few fishermen collect their crabbing cages by the bank.
A fisherman picks the crabs from the cage, which are of similar sizes as those sold in market.
Two egrets walk around the river bank.

enTitle: A Little Girl in Korean Costume
enDesc: There are a few venders lending North Korean costumes. A little girl has her photo taken in costumes.
Yalu River is shared by China and North Korea, so boats of both sides can drive freely. Some chinese tourist boats offer driving very close to North Korean river bank.
A gentle man walks along the river bank, with a cane, a smoking pipe, and a coat. He stands out from the tourists crowd.
“LOVE” of a wedding. At least both contain the correct four characters.

enTitle: A Train from North Korea to China
enDesc: A train drives from North Korea into China, with its siren on.
The North Korean train has one locomotive and one compartment.
The houses by the side of the street along Yalu River. It seems like those kind of houses I stayed in as a child, and I have a little memory of that clock tower.

enTitle: Plastic Stone Inscribed with Yalu River
enDesc: The “stone” inscribed with “Yalu River” is made in plastic. There are wheels on the bottom so it can be pushed away at night. It’s fixed on the pole by rope.
